[Tool call: read_file({file_path: "src/middleware/auth.ts"})]

I can see the issue. On line 23, you're checking `token.exp > Date.now()` but `token.exp` is in seconds (JWT standard) while `Date.now()` returns milliseconds. The comparison will always be true because milliseconds > seconds.

The fix is to compare in the same unit:
```ts
if (token.exp * 1000 < Date.now()) {
  return res.status(401).json({ error: 'Token expired' });
}
```

